[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 14
[CLAUDE] tags: [auth, session, jwt, password, email-verification]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Authentication System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Handles all user identity flows: registration, login, session management, and credential recovery.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Flows
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Registration (`/api/auth/signup`)
[CLAUDE] 1. POST `{ name, email, password, organizationName, organizationSlug }`
[CLAUDE] 2. `registerUserWithOrganization()` creates user + org atomically
[CLAUDE] 3. `sendSignupNotificationsFromDatabase()` sends welcome + verification email
[CLAUDE] 4. Session cookie set on success
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Login (`/api/auth/login`)
[CLAUDE] 1. POST `{ email, password }`
[CLAUDE] 2. `authenticateUser()` validates credentials
[CLAUDE] 3. Session cookie (`getSessionCookieName()`) set with expiry from `getSessionExpirationDate()`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Session Validation
[CLAUDE] - **Web app**: `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest()` — reads session cookie
[CLAUDE] - **Extension**: `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest()` — reads `Authorization` header token
[CLAUDE] - Session data available at `GET /api/auth/session`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Password Recovery
[CLAUDE] | Step | Endpoint | Service |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Request reset | `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` | `sendForgotPasswordNotificationFromDatabase()` |
[CLAUDE] | Complete reset | `POST /api/auth/reset-password` | `completePasswordResetFromTokenInDatabase()` |
[CLAUDE] | Change password | `POST /api/auth/change-password` | `changeAuthenticatedUserPasswordInDatabase()` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Tokens stored via `auth-action-token-store.ts` with expiry.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Email Verification
[CLAUDE] - `POST /api/auth/verify-email` with `{ token }`
[CLAUDE] - `verifyEmailAddressFromTokenInDatabase()` marks address as verified
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Logout
[CLAUDE] - `POST /api/auth/logout` — deletes server-side session, clears cookie
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Role |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/auth/auth-service.ts` | Core: `authenticateUser`, `requireAdminUser`, `requireAuthenticatedUser` |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/auth/session.ts` | Cookie name, expiry, max-age helpers |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/auth/auth-user-store.ts` | User persistence layer |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/auth/auth-action-token-store.ts` | One-time tokens (reset, verify) |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/auth/password.ts` | Hashing utilities |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Authorization Guards
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `requireAuthenticatedUser()` — any logged-in user
[CLAUDE] - `requireAdminUser()` — platform admin (used by all `/api/admin/*` routes)
[CLAUDE] - `requireAgentApiUser()` — agent API key auth (used by `/api/agent/*` routes)
[CLAUDE] - `requireActiveOrganizationSession()` — user with active org context
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/bugs/bug-management.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 20
[CLAUDE] tags: [bugs, crud, comments, attachments, history, import, export]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Management
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Core domain: creating, reading, updating, and tracking software bugs.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Data Model (key fields)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Field | Type | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `id` | number | Primary key |
[CLAUDE] | `title` | string | Required |
[CLAUDE] | `description` | string | Required |
[CLAUDE] | `severity` | string | e.g. `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical` |
[CLAUDE] | `status` | string | `New` → `Triaged` → `In Progress` → `Ready for QA` → `Closed` |
[CLAUDE] | `reporterUserId` | number | User who filed it |
[CLAUDE] | `assigneeUserId` | number \| null | Assigned engineer |
[CLAUDE] | `projectId` | number | Required |
[CLAUDE] | `sectionId` | number | Project section |
[CLAUDE] | `is_archived` | boolean | Soft delete |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## API Surface (`/api/bugs/*`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Action |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs` | List bugs (filterable) |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs` | Create bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Update bug fields |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/bulk` | Bulk status update |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | List comments |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | Add comment |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments` | Upload attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Download attachment |
[CLAUDE] | DELETE | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Delete attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/history` | Audit timeline |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug List Filters (`all-bugs-filters.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Filters available on the list view:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `projectId` — positive integer
[CLAUDE] - `status` — one of `BUG_FILTER_STATUSES`
[CLAUDE] - `reporterUserId` — positive integer
[CLAUDE] - `startDate` / `endDate` — ISO date strings
[CLAUDE] - `showArchived` — boolean
[CLAUDE] - `sortField` — `createdAt` | `updatedAt` | `status` | `project`
[CLAUDE] - `sortDirection` — `asc` | `desc`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Default sort: `createdAt desc`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug History / Audit Trail
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `GET /api/bugs/[bugId]/history` returns a timeline of `BugHistoryTimelineEntry` objects. Each entry includes:
[CLAUDE] - `eventType` — e.g. `bug_created`, `bug_status_changed`, `bug_import_*`
[CLAUDE] - `changedFields[]` — `{ field, previousValue, nextValue }`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Source: `bug-history-service.ts` + `bug-history-store.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] History entry source is derived by `getBugHistoryEntrySource()`:
[CLAUDE] - `bug_import_*` events → "Import"
[CLAUDE] - `bug_*` events → "User"
[CLAUDE] - Other → "System"
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bulk Operations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `PATCH /api/bugs/bulk` accepts `{ bugIds: number[], status: string }` — updates status on multiple bugs at once.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Comments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Comments have a `visibility` field (public/internal). Listed at `GET /api/bugs/[bugId]/comments`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Attachments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Files stored via `attachmentStorage` (configured in `src/lib/storage/`). The store layer is `attachment-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Import / Export
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Managed via `bug-data-import-service.ts` and `bug-data-export-service.ts`. Jobs tracked in `bug-data-job-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Job statuses: `queued` → `running` → `completed` | `completed_with_warnings` | `failed`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Export manifest includes: bug count, history entry count, attachment count, missing file count.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Import supports duplicate strategies: `skip_existing` | `update_existing`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Service Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Role |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/bug-service.ts` | Core CRUD: `createBug`, `getBugById`, `updateBug`, `listBugs`, `bulkUpdateBugs` |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/bug-comment-service.ts` | Comment management |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/bug-history-service.ts` | Timeline entries |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/bug-data-import-service.ts` | CSV/batch import |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/bug-data-export-service.ts` | Export to archive |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/bugs/errors.ts` | `BugServiceError` typed errors |
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
