[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 8
[CLAUDE] tags: [database, postgresql, schema, migrations, testing]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Database Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app uses **PostgreSQL** as its primary database. For unit tests, an **in-memory SQLite** backend is available to avoid Docker dependency.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database Client Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] PostgreSQL access is intentionally isolated in a **Worker thread** to avoid connection pool issues in Next.js serverless/edge environments:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Next.js Request Handler
[CLAUDE]   └── getDatabase()           [src/lib/db/index.ts]
[CLAUDE]        └── postgres-client.ts — decides backend from env
[CLAUDE]             ├── PostgresWorker (prod/integration)
[CLAUDE]             │    └── postgres-worker.ts  [Worker thread]
[CLAUDE]             │         └── pg (node-postgres)
[CLAUDE]             └── LocalTestDatabase (unit tests, in-memory)
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The worker is pre-built to `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs` during `npm run build` and `predev`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Backend Selection
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Set via environment variable:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND=memory    # in-memory SQLite (unit tests)
[CLAUDE] BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND=postgres  # real PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] (unset)                               # defaults to PostgreSQL in production
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Role |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/schema.ts` | TypeScript schema definitions |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-schema.ts` | PostgreSQL DDL schema |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-client.ts` | PostgreSQL client setup |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-worker.ts` | Worker thread entry point |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-config.ts` | Config from env vars |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` | Shared client interface |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/local-test-database.ts` | In-memory SQLite for tests |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/bootstrap-admin.ts` | Admin seed on first run |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-bootstrap.ts` | Schema bootstrap |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Migrations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run against local PostgreSQL:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] This executes `scripts/migrate-postgres.ts` using env from `.env`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Local Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Start PostgreSQL via Docker Compose
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Apply migrations
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Default connection: `127.0.0.1:5432` (from `.env.example`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Test Strategy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **Fast unit tests** (`npm test`): use in-memory backend, no Docker required
[CLAUDE] - **PostgreSQL unit tests** (`npm run test:unit:postgres`): require running container, run via `scripts/run-postgres-unit-tests.sh`
[CLAUDE] - **E2E tests**: seed via `npm run test:e2e:seed`, run against real DB at port 3001
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
