[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 12
[CLAUDE] tags: [monitoring, observability, alerts, performance, logging, errors]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Monitoring & Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The monitoring subsystem captures structured operational events, groups errors by fingerprint, tracks endpoint performance, and surfaces operational alerts.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Request Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every API route is wrapped with `withRequestObservability(method, handler)` from `src/lib/monitoring/request-observability.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] This wrapper:
[CLAUDE] - Logs request timing
[CLAUDE] - Captures errors with context
[CLAUDE] - Emits structured NDJSON to `log/observability.ndjson`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Client-side page load timing is reported to `POST /api/observability/page-load` and handled by the `PageLoadObservability` component.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Structured Logging
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Events are written via `observability-logger-service.ts` to a file sink (`observability-file-sink.ts`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Log format: NDJSON at `log/observability.ndjson`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sensitive fields are redacted before logging via `observability-redaction.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Severity levels: `debug` | `info` | `warn` | `error` | `critical`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Error Grouping
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Errors are grouped by fingerprint using `error-fingerprint.ts`. The `grouped-errors-service.ts` provides:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `getGroupedErrors()` — aggregated error clusters
[CLAUDE] - `getErrorGroupEntries()` — individual log entries within a group
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Valid severities for error grouping: `error` | `critical`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Accessible via admin panel at `/admin/monitoring` and `GET /api/admin/errors`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Operational Alerts
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alerts represent actionable conditions that may require human response.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Concept | File |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Alert CRUD | `operational-alert-store.ts` |
[CLAUDE] | Business logic | `operational-alert-service.ts` |
[CLAUDE] | CLI tool | `operational-alert-cli.ts` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Filters: `severity`, `status`, `source`, `latestSeenFrom`, `latestSeenTo`, `limit` (default 25).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alerts can be **linked to bugs** via `POST /api/admin/alerts/[alertId]/bugs` — this calls `createBugFromOperationalAlert()`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alert status can be updated via `PATCH /api/admin/alerts/[alertId]`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Endpoint Performance
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `endpoint-performance-service.ts` aggregates response time metrics by endpoint. Supports time window filtering via `isValidWindow()`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Accessible at `GET /api/admin/performance/endpoints`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Dashboard Summary
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `dashboard-summary-service.ts` provides aggregated metrics for the admin dashboard at `GET /api/admin/dashboard/summary`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organisation Usage
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `org-usage-service.ts` provides per-org usage statistics at `GET /api/admin/performance/org-usage`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability Event Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Defined in `observability-event.ts` — the canonical shape of a logged event flowing through the system.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
