[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Agent Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The platform exposes a dedicated API surface and tooling for automated (AI/agent) bug operations.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent API (`/api/agent/*`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Authentication uses API key auth via `requireAgentApiUser()` (distinct from session-cookie auth used by the web app).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Helper functions in `src/lib/bugs/agent-api.ts`:
[CLAUDE] - `requireAgentApiUser()` — validate API key
[CLAUDE] - `parseAgentBugId()` — parse and validate bug ID
[CLAUDE] - `createAgentApiSuccessResponse()` / `createAgentApiErrorResponse()` — standard response shapes
[CLAUDE] - `handleAgentApiError()` — typed error handling
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Endpoints
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs` | List claimable bugs (`listClaimableBugs()`) |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` | Claim a bug: `{ claimedBy: string }` |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/status` | Update work status: `{ claimedBy, state, statusNote? }` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## MCP Server
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts` implements a **Model Context Protocol** server exposing bug tracker tools to AI agents.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run via: `npm run mcp:server` → `scripts/mcp-server.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] This allows Claude and other MCP-compatible agents to interact with the bug tracker as a tool.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent CLI
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/agent-cli.ts` provides a command-line interface for agent operations.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run via: `npm run bugs:cli` → `scripts/bug-agent-cli.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent Integration Module
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/agent-integration.ts` contains shared integration logic used by both the API and CLI.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Alerts CLI
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/monitoring/operational-alert-cli.ts` provides CLI access to operational alerts.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run via: `npm run alerts:cli` → `scripts/alerts-cli.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The extension and agent can create **testing sessions** to group evidence (attachments, logs) captured during a QA run:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Role |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `testing-session-service.ts` | Session lifecycle |
[CLAUDE] | `testing-session-store.ts` | Persistence |
[CLAUDE] | `testing-session-log-service.ts` | Log entries within a session |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Vision (from Product Docs)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See [Agent Vision](../../../concepts/bug_tracker-agent-vision.md) for the planned roadmap toward multi-agent, autonomous bug triage and investigation.
