[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Chrome Extension
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A browser extension enabling users to submit bugs and attach evidence directly from their browser.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Role |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `extension/manifest.json` | Chrome extension manifest |
[CLAUDE] | `extension/popup.html` + `popup.js` + `popup.css` | Extension popup UI |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## API Surface (`/api/extension/*`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The extension has its own API surface, separate from the web app, using **Bearer token auth** (not session cookies).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/login` | Login, returns auth token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/logout` | Logout |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/auth/session` | Get current session |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/projects` | List available projects |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/bugs` | Submit a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` | Attach evidence to a bug during a testing session |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/version` | Extension version check |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Version Management
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/extension/extension-version.ts` — version compatibility checking between extension and server.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/extension/extension-service.ts` — service layer for extension operations.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Session Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] When a testing session is active, evidence (screenshots, recordings) submitted via `POST /api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` is associated with both the bug and the active testing session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Requires `requireActiveBugTestingSession()` guard from `testing-session-service.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Install Guide
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] User-facing install instructions are surfaced at `/chrome-extension` and via the dashboard's `extension-install-panel.tsx`.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
