[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Local Development Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Prerequisites
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Node.js (LTS)
[CLAUDE] - npm
[CLAUDE] - Docker + Docker Compose
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## First-Time Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # 1. Clone repo and install dependencies
[CLAUDE] npm install
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 2. Create local env file
[CLAUDE] cp .env.example .env
[CLAUDE] # Edit .env if needed — defaults work for local PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 3. Start PostgreSQL container
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 4. Apply database migrations
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 5. Start dev server
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Open `http://localhost:3000`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Daily Workflow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Start dependencies
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Start dev server (automatically builds DB worker first)
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Running Tests
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Fast unit tests (in-memory DB, no Docker needed)
[CLAUDE] npm test
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # PostgreSQL-backed unit tests (requires running container)
[CLAUDE] npm run test:unit:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # E2E tests
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e:seed      # seed test database
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e           # run Playwright tests
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e:headed    # run with visible browser
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e:ui        # Playwright UI mode
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Code Quality
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run lint        # ESLint
[CLAUDE] npm run typecheck   # TypeScript + Next.js type generation
[CLAUDE] npm run ci          # Full local CI (lint + typecheck + test)
[CLAUDE] npm run ci:quick    # Skip slower checks
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Production Build
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run build   # Next.js build + DB worker bundle
[CLAUDE] npm run start   # Serve production build
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Environment Variables
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Key variables (from `.env.example`):
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Variable | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `DATABASE_URL` or `POSTGRES_*` | PostgreSQL connection |
[CLAUDE] | `SENDGRID_API_KEY` | Email delivery (optional for local) |
[CLAUDE] | `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND` | `memory` for unit tests |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Troubleshooting
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **DB connection refused**: Ensure `docker compose up -d postgres` is running
[CLAUDE] - **Worker build errors**: Run `npm run build:db-worker` manually
[CLAUDE] - **Type errors**: Run `npm run typecheck` — it regenerates Next.js types first
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
