[CLAUDE] # Deployment
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app runs as a standard Next.js production server behind an Nginx reverse proxy.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Full deployment details are in the repository at `docs/deployment-nginx.md`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Production Start
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Build application + DB worker bundle
[CLAUDE] npm run build
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Start production server
[CLAUDE] npm run start
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database Migrations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run migrations against production PostgreSQL before starting the app:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] node --env-file=.env --import tsx scripts/migrate-postgres.ts
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Or via npm script (requires `.env`):
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Nginx Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See `docs/deployment-nginx.md` for:
[CLAUDE] - Domain-based routing configuration
[CLAUDE] - SSL termination
[CLAUDE] - Reverse proxy to `http://localhost:3000`
[CLAUDE] - Named tunnel setup via `tunnel-cli` (Cloudflare Tunnel)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Exposing Locally via Tunnel
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Use `tunnel-cli` (at `~/RanjanWork/tunnel-cli`) to expose the local dev server:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] tunnel expose 3000       # Quick HTTPS URL (trycloudflare.com)
[CLAUDE] tunnel start myapp 3000  # Stable named tunnel (requires Cloudflare login)
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability in Production
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Structured logs written to `log/observability.ndjson`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See `docs/observability.md` for log rotation, monitoring configuration, and alerting setup.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Bootstrap
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] First run: `src/lib/db/bootstrap-admin.ts` seeds the initial admin user. Configure credentials via environment variables before first boot.
