[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/concepts/bug_tracker-domain-model.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: concept
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 5
[CLAUDE] tags: [domain-model, bugs, organizations, projects, glossary]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Domain Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Entity Hierarchy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Organization
[CLAUDE]   └── has many Users (via Membership)
[CLAUDE]   └── has many Projects
[CLAUDE]        └── has many ProjectSections
[CLAUDE]             └── has many Bugs
[CLAUDE]                  ├── has many Comments
[CLAUDE]                  ├── has many Attachments
[CLAUDE]                  └── has many HistoryEntries
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core Entities
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Organization
[CLAUDE] The top-level tenant. All data is scoped to an org. Users switch between orgs via the org switcher. Created during signup.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Project
[CLAUDE] Belongs to an org. Groups related bugs. Has **sections** (columns/phases) for organizing bugs within a project.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Bug
[CLAUDE] The primary work item. Key attributes:
[CLAUDE] - **Status lifecycle**: `New` → `Triaged` → `In Progress` → `Ready for QA` → `Closed`
[CLAUDE] - **Severity**: `low` | `medium` | `high` | `critical`
[CLAUDE] - **Archived**: soft-deleted bugs hidden by default
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### BugHistory
[CLAUDE] Immutable audit trail for a bug. Each entry records `eventType` and `changedFields` with `previousValue` / `nextValue`. Sources: user action, import, system.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### TestingSession
[CLAUDE] A bounded QA session where evidence (screenshots, logs) is captured and linked to bugs. Created by the extension or agent during testing.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### OperationalAlert
[CLAUDE] A monitoring signal that may require human action. Can be linked to a bug. Has a status lifecycle (open → acknowledged → resolved).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## User Roles
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Role | Access |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Platform Admin | All `/api/admin/*` routes, full system access |
[CLAUDE] | Org Admin | Organization management, member access control |
[CLAUDE] | Member | Bug CRUD within assigned projects |
[CLAUDE] | Agent | Machine-to-machine via `/api/agent/*` (API key) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Status Enumerations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Bug statuses** (ordered): `New`, `Triaged`, `In Progress`, `Ready for QA`, `Closed`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Bug data job statuses**: `queued` → `running` → `completed` | `completed_with_warnings` | `failed`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Alert statuses**: open / acknowledged / resolved (managed via `OperationalAlertStatus` type)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Notification delivery statuses**: tracked in `notification-store.ts`
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/concepts/bug_tracker-agent-vision.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: concept
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 1
[CLAUDE] tags: [agent, ai, vision, roadmap, multi-agent]
[CLAUDE] status: draft
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Agent Vision & Roadmap
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sourced from `shared/agent_bugtracker.md` — the product vision for evolving the bug tracker into an AI-powered operations platform.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Planned Agent Capabilities
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 1. Intelligent Bug Intake
[CLAUDE] Transform messy reports into structured bugs:
[CLAUDE] - Auto-extract steps to reproduce from chat, email, or voice notes
[CLAUDE] - Detect missing details before submission
[CLAUDE] - Rewrite vague titles to clear, specific ones
[CLAUDE] - Auto-classify severity, priority, module, and likely owner
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 2. Duplicate & Pattern Detection
[CLAUDE] - Match similar titles, logs, stack traces, and session replays
[CLAUDE] - Group related reports into a parent incident with confidence scores
[CLAUDE] - Reduce ticket noise dramatically
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 3. Evidence Aggregation
[CLAUDE] Connect bugs to real evidence automatically:
[CLAUDE] - API failures, logs, deployment history, feature flags
[CLAUDE] - Session recordings, screenshots, test failures
[CLAUDE] - Enable statements like: *"This bug started appearing 23 min after release 2.4.8"*
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 4. Triage Authority
[CLAUDE] First-pass automated triage:
[CLAUDE] - Classify as bug / feature request / support issue / user error
[CLAUDE] - Auto-assign to correct team
[CLAUDE] - Modes: conservative (suggest only) → assisted (human approval) → autonomous
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 5. Root Cause Investigation
[CLAUDE] Analyze commits, PRs, deployments, and past bugs to produce hypotheses with confidence scores.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 6. Multi-Team Coordination
[CLAUDE] Generate role-specific views of a single issue:
[CLAUDE] - Engineering: technical root cause
[CLAUDE] - Product: user impact count
[CLAUDE] - Support: customer-safe summary
[CLAUDE] - QA: verification steps
[CLAUDE] - Leadership: release risk assessment
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### 7. Post-Fix Tracking
[CLAUDE] Continue monitoring after resolution:
[CLAUDE] - Verify fix reduced occurrences
[CLAUDE] - Watch for regressions
[CLAUDE] - Auto-draft postmortem summaries and release notes
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Proposed Specialist Agent Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Rather than one general agent, a fleet of focused agents:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Agent | Responsibility |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Intake Agent | Structure and clean bug reports |
[CLAUDE] | Triage Agent | Prioritize and route |
[CLAUDE] | Investigation Agent | Analyze logs, code changes, deployments |
[CLAUDE] | QA Agent | Suggest test scenarios and verification steps |
[CLAUDE] | Release Agent | Assess release risk |
[CLAUDE] | Support Agent | Draft customer-facing communications |
[CLAUDE] | Insights Agent | Surface recurring patterns and quality trends |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Current Implementation
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The MCP server (`src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts`) and agent API (`/api/agent/*`) form the foundation for this vision. The agent can currently claim bugs and update their status programmatically.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
