[CLAUDE] # Bug Tracker — System Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bug Tracker is a Next.js 16 application for capturing, triaging, and managing software issues inside an authenticated workspace. It is a full-stack monorepo: the browser app, all API routes, and background tooling live in a single Next.js project.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Tech Stack
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Layer | Technology |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Framework | Next.js 16 (webpack mode) |
[CLAUDE] | Language | TypeScript 5 |
[CLAUDE] | UI | React 19, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui |
[CLAUDE] | Database | PostgreSQL (primary), in-memory SQLite (tests) |
[CLAUDE] | Email | SendGrid |
[CLAUDE] | Runtime tooling | tsx, esbuild, node:test |
[CLAUDE] | E2E testing | Playwright |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Major Subsystems
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Subsystem | Path | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Auth | `src/lib/auth/` | Login, signup, sessions, password flows, email verification |
[CLAUDE] | Bugs | `src/lib/bugs/` | CRUD, comments, attachments, history, bulk ops, import/export |
[CLAUDE] | Organizations | `src/lib/organizations/` | Org creation, membership, invitations, billing, seat management |
[CLAUDE] | Projects | `src/lib/projects/` | Project + section management, membership |
[CLAUDE] | Monitoring | `src/lib/monitoring/` | Observability events, operational logs, alerts, performance |
[CLAUDE] | Notifications | `src/lib/notifications/` | Email dispatch via SendGrid, template engine, delivery history |
[CLAUDE] | Settings | `src/lib/settings/` | API keys, JWT auth config, API access policy |
[CLAUDE] | Extension | `src/lib/extension/` | Chrome extension auth and bug submission |
[CLAUDE] | Agent API | `src/lib/bugs/agent-api.ts` | Programmatic bug operations for automated agents |
[CLAUDE] | MCP Server | `src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts` | Model Context Protocol server for LLM tool access |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Entry Points
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **Browser app**: `src/app/(authenticated)/` — all authenticated workspace pages
[CLAUDE] - **REST API**: `src/app/api/` — Next.js route handlers
[CLAUDE] - **Admin surfaces**: `src/app/(authenticated)/admin/`
[CLAUDE] - **CLI scripts**: `scripts/` — bug agent CLI, alerts CLI, MCP server
[CLAUDE] - **Chrome extension**: `extension/`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database Backends
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app supports two backends selected via `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND`:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `memory` — in-memory SQLite for fast unit tests (default for `npm test`)
[CLAUDE] - `postgres` — PostgreSQL for production and integration tests
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See [database schema](./database/schema.md) and [local setup runbook](../../runbooks/bug_tracker-local-setup.md).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Related Pages
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - [API Endpoints](./api/endpoints.md)
[CLAUDE] - [Authentication](./auth/authentication.md)
[CLAUDE] - [Bug Management](./bugs/bug-management.md)
