[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # API Endpoints
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All API routes live under `src/app/api/` and are Next.js App Router route handlers. Every handler is wrapped with `withRequestObservability` which records request timing and errors to the operational log.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth (`/api/auth/`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/signup` | Register user + create organization; sets session cookie |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/login` | Authenticate user; sets session cookie |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/logout` | Delete session; clears cookie |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/auth/session` | Return current session user |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/verify-email` | Confirm email token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | Send reset link |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/reset-password` | Complete reset via token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/auth/change-password` | Change password for authenticated user |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bugs (`/api/bugs/`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/bugs` | List bugs (filterable: projectId, status, reporter, dates, sort) |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs` | Create bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Get single bug |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Update bug fields |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/bulk` | Bulk-update bug statuses |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | List comments |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | Add comment |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[attachmentId]` | Download attachment |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments` | Upload attachment |
[CLAUDE] | DELETE | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[attachmentId]` | Delete attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/history` | Bug change timeline (admin only) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent API (`/api/agent/bugs/`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Authenticated via API key. Used by automated agents.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/agent/bugs` | List claimable bugs |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` | Claim a bug (`claimedBy`) |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/status` | Update agent work state/note |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin (`/api/admin/`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Requires admin session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/projects` | List / create projects |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]` | Update project |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]/sections` | List / create sections |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/projects/[projectId]/sections/[sectionId]` | Update section |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/admin/users` | List / create QA users |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/users/[userId]/deactivate` | Deactivate user |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/dashboard/summary` | Dashboard metrics |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/logs` | Operational log entries (paginated) |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/errors` | Grouped error fingerprints |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/admin/errors/[fingerprint]/bug` | Link error group to a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/alerts` | List operational alerts |
[CLAUDE] | GET/PATCH | `/api/admin/alerts/[alertId]` | Get / update alert status |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/alerts/[alertId]/bugs` | Create bug from alert |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/performance/endpoints` | Endpoint latency stats |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/performance/org-usage` | Per-org usage stats |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/notifications/deliveries` | Notification delivery history |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/notifications/deliveries/[id]/retry` | Retry delivery |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/admin/notifications/events/[id]/retry` | Retry notification event |
[CLAUDE] | GET/PATCH | `/api/admin/notifications/settings` | Get / update notification settings |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/admin/organizations-with-projects` | Org + project list for admin |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension (`/api/extension/`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Used by the Chrome extension; auth via Bearer token in header.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/login` | Authenticate from extension |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/logout` | Deauthenticate |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/extension/auth/session` | Current session |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/extension/projects` | List projects for extension |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/extension/bugs` | List / submit bugs |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` | Upload screenshot evidence |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/extension/version` | Extension version check |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organizations & Invitations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/organizations` | List / create organizations |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/organizations/active` | Active organization for session |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/organizations/invitations` | List / create invitations |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/organizations/[id]` | Get organization |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/projects` | List / create projects (user-scoped) |
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST | `/api/invitations/activate` | Activate invitation |
[CLAUDE] | GET  | `/api/invitations/[token]` | Get invitation by token |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Settings
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET/POST/DELETE | `/api/settings/api-access` | Manage API keys and JWT config |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/observability/page-load` | Client-side page load timing |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Request Validation Pattern
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All handlers validate request bodies before touching the database. Shape checks use plain TypeScript `typeof` guards — no Zod at the boundary. Invalid requests return `400`. Auth failures return `401`. Service-layer errors (typed error classes) map to `400`/`404`/`409`.
