[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/auth/authentication.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 14
[CLAUDE] tags: [auth, sessions, jwt, password, email-verification]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Authentication System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Authentication is handled entirely in `src/lib/auth/`. There is no external auth provider — users, sessions, and tokens are stored in PostgreSQL.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Session Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sessions use an HTTP-only cookie. The cookie name and expiration are configured via `src/lib/auth/session.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionCookieName()` — returns the cookie name
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionMaxAgeSeconds()` — session duration in seconds
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionExpirationDate()` — computed expiry `Date`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] On login/signup, a session token is written to the database and set as a cookie. On logout, the token is deleted from the database and the cookie is cleared.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The session is read from request cookies in `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest()`. For the Chrome extension, `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest()` reads a Bearer token from the `Authorization` header instead.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Service (`auth-service.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Core functions:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Function | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `authenticateUser(db, {email, password})` | Verify credentials, create session, return token |
[CLAUDE] | `registerUserWithOrganization(db, {...})` | Create user + org atomically, create session |
[CLAUDE] | `requireAuthenticatedUser(request)` | Throw `AuthenticationError` if no valid session |
[CLAUDE] | `requireAdminUser(request)` | Throw if not admin |
[CLAUDE] | `requireExtensionAuthenticatedUser(request)` | For extension Bearer auth |
[CLAUDE] | `deleteSessionByToken(token)` | Logout |
[CLAUDE] | `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest(request)` | Returns session or null |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `AuthenticationError` is the typed error class; callers map it to 401.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Password Handling
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Passwords are hashed in `src/lib/auth/password.ts`. The hash algorithm is bcrypt (inferred from standard Next.js auth patterns).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Password flows:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **Forgot password** (`forgot-password-service.ts`): generates a token, stores it via `auth-action-token-store.ts`, sends email via `auth-notification-service.ts`
[CLAUDE] - **Reset password** (`reset-password-service.ts`): validates token, updates hash
[CLAUDE] - **Change password** (`change-password-service.ts`): requires current password, updates hash for authenticated user
[CLAUDE] - **Email verification** (`email-verification-service.ts`): token-based, same token store
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Action Token Store
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/auth/auth-action-token-store.ts` stores short-lived tokens (password reset, email verification) in the database. Each token has a type, expiry, and single-use flag.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Notification Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/auth/auth-notification-service.ts` sends transactional emails on:
[CLAUDE] - Signup (welcome)
[CLAUDE] - Email verification
[CLAUDE] - Forgot password
[CLAUDE] - Password changed
[CLAUDE] - Password reset complete
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] These delegate to the [notification system](../notifications/email-notifications.md).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension Auth
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The Chrome extension cannot use cookies (cross-origin). It authenticates via `/api/extension/auth/login`, receives an API token, and sends it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on subsequent requests.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Auth
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin access checks `user.isAdmin` from the session. There is no separate role table — it is a boolean on the user record, set during QA user creation or bootstrap.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bootstrap
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/bootstrap-admin.ts` seeds the first admin user for a fresh deployment.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/bugs/bug-management.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 20
[CLAUDE] tags: [bugs, comments, attachments, history, import, export, testing-session]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Management
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The bug subsystem lives in `src/lib/bugs/`. It covers the full lifecycle: creation, triage, comments, attachments, history tracking, bulk operations, data import/export, and agent-driven work.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Service (`bug-service.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Central service. Key operations:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Function | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `createBug` | Create bug, record initial history event |
[CLAUDE] | `getBugById` | Fetch single bug with org membership check |
[CLAUDE] | `listBugs` | Filtered, sorted, paginated list |
[CLAUDE] | `updateBug` | Update fields, record history diff |
[CLAUDE] | `bulkUpdateBugs` | Status update for multiple bugs at once |
[CLAUDE] | `deleteBugAttachment` | Remove attachment file + record |
[CLAUDE] | `getAttachmentForBug` | Retrieve attachment with access check |
[CLAUDE] | `createBugAttachment` | Store uploaded file |
[CLAUDE] | `listClaimableBugs` | Agent-facing: bugs available for agent pickup |
[CLAUDE] | `claimBug` | Mark bug as claimed by an agent |
[CLAUDE] | `updateBugAgentWork` | Update agent state/note on a bug |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `BugServiceError` is thrown for domain violations (not found, permission denied, invalid state).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Status Values
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs can also be archived (`is_archived`). Archived bugs are excluded from default list queries unless `showArchived=true`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Severity Levels
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Defined in filter constants: used in `all-bugs-filters.ts`. Displayed via `components/bugs/severity-badge.tsx` and `components/bugs/status-badge.tsx`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Comments (`bug-comment-service.ts`, `bug-comment-store.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Comments have a `body` and optional `visibility` field (e.g., internal vs. public). `createBugComment` fires notification events.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Attachments (`attachment-store.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Attachment metadata is stored in the database. File bytes are stored via `src/lib/storage/attachment-storage.ts`. The storage module is abstracted behind `src/lib/storage/index.ts` so the backend can be swapped (local disk, S3, etc.).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## History (`bug-history-service.ts`, `bug-history-store.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every mutation to a bug is recorded as a history event. `listBugHistoryTimelineEntries` returns a timeline with:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `eventType` — e.g. `bug_created`, `bug_status_changed`, `bug_import_created`
[CLAUDE] - `changedFields` — array of `{ field, previousValue, nextValue }`
[CLAUDE] - source attribution (user, agent, or import)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Helper functions in `src/app/(authenticated)/bugs/[bugId]/bug-history.helpers.ts` format events for display.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Import / Export (`bug-data-import-service.ts`, `bug-data-export-service.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admins can bulk-import bugs from CSV and export bugs to a ZIP archive.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Import flow:**
[CLAUDE] 1. Upload CSV → validation pass (returns `BugImportValidationResult` with per-row issues)
[CLAUDE] 2. If valid, execute import → `BugImportExecutionResult` with counts (created/updated/skipped/failed)
[CLAUDE] 3. Duplicate strategy: `skip_existing` or `update_existing`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Export flow:**
[CLAUDE] 1. Request export → creates job record in `bug-data-job-store.ts`
[CLAUDE] 2. Job runs, produces ZIP at `resultFilePath`
[CLAUDE] 3. Manifest records bug count, history entries, attachments, missing files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Jobs are tracked in `BugDataManagementJob` with statuses: `queued → running → completed | completed_with_warnings | failed`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions (`testing-session-service.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A testing session groups bugs submitted by a tester during a defined time window. The extension uses this to correlate bugs reported in the same session. Sessions have a log (`testing-session-log-service.ts`) recording actions taken during the session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Filters (`all-bugs-filters.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `AllBugsFilterState` covers: projectId, status, reporterUserId, startDate, endDate, showArchived, sortField, sortDirection.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `buildAllBugSearchParams` serialises filters to URL search params. `parseAllBugFilters` parses them back. `validateAllBugFilters` throws on invalid values before any DB call.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sort fields: `createdAt | updatedAt | status | project`. Sort directions: `asc | desc`.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
