[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Notification System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The notification subsystem lives in `src/lib/notifications/`. It handles all transactional email delivery via SendGrid and the admin interface for reviewing delivery history and settings.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Bug event / Auth event
[CLAUDE]        ↓
[CLAUDE] BugNotificationEventService   ← decides which notifications to send
[CLAUDE]        ↓
[CLAUDE] NotificationDispatcher        ← resolves recipients and settings
[CLAUDE]        ↓
[CLAUDE] SendGridDelivery              ← sends via SendGrid API
[CLAUDE]        ↓
[CLAUDE] NotificationStore             ← persists event + delivery records
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Event Types
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bug-related notification events:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `bug_created` | `bug-created.html` |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_assigned` | `bug-assigned.html` |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_status_changed` | `bug-status-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_closed` | `bug-closed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_reopened` | `bug-reopened.html` |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_comment` | `bug-comment.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Auth-related:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Signup welcome | `welcome.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Email verification | `verification.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Forgot password | `forgot-password.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password changed | `password-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password reset complete | `password-reset-complete.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Organization invitation | `organization-invitation.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Template Engine (`template-engine.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Templates are HTML files in `src/lib/notifications/templates/`. They extend `base-layout.html`. Variables are interpolated by the template engine — no external templating library.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `email-template-registry.ts` maps event types to template files.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Recipient Resolution (`bug-recipient-service.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `BugRecipientService` determines who receives a notification for a given bug event: the reporter, assignee, project members, and any watchers, subject to per-recipient notification preferences.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Notification Settings
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admins control which event types are enabled for which recipient groups via `GET/PATCH /api/admin/notifications/settings`. Settings are stored in the database.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Delivery History
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every send attempt is recorded as a delivery record with status (`pending | sent | failed`). Admins can view delivery history and retry failed deliveries or events via:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `POST /api/admin/notifications/deliveries/[id]/retry`
[CLAUDE] - `POST /api/admin/notifications/events/[id]/retry`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Filters on the delivery list: eventType, deliveryStatus, recipientEmail, limit.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## SendGrid Configuration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] SendGrid API key and sender address are set via environment variables. Leave them empty for local development unless testing email flows. See `.env.example`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Notification Flow Test
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/notifications/bug-notification-flow.test.ts` is an integration test for the full notification pipeline.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
