[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 5
[CLAUDE] tags: [chrome-extension, browser-extension, evidence]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Chrome Extension
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The Chrome extension allows testers to report bugs directly from any web page without switching to the bug tracker UI.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] extension/
[CLAUDE] ├── manifest.json   — extension manifest (Manifest V3)
[CLAUDE] ├── popup.html      — extension popup UI
[CLAUDE] ├── popup.css       — popup styles
[CLAUDE] └── popup.js        — popup logic
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] There is also an install guide page at `src/app/chrome-extension/page.tsx` and a dashboard prompt in `src/app/(authenticated)/dashboard/extension-install-panel.tsx`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Authentication
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The extension cannot share cookies with the web app (cross-origin). It authenticates separately:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. User opens popup, enters credentials
[CLAUDE] 2. Extension calls `POST /api/extension/auth/login` → receives a session token
[CLAUDE] 3. Token is stored in extension storage and sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on all subsequent requests
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Logout: `POST /api/extension/auth/logout` invalidates the server-side session.
[CLAUDE] Session check: `GET /api/extension/auth/session` returns current user or 401.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Submission
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] From the popup:
[CLAUDE] 1. `GET /api/extension/projects` — load available projects
[CLAUDE] 2. User fills out bug form
[CLAUDE] 3. `POST /api/extension/bugs` — submit bug
[CLAUDE] 4. Optional: `POST /api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` — upload screenshot
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Evidence uploads attach the image to the bug and link it to the active testing session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Version Check
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `GET /api/extension/version` returns the expected extension version. The extension service (`src/lib/extension/extension-service.ts`) and version module (`src/lib/extension/extension-version.ts`) manage version compatibility checks — useful for prompting users to update an outdated extension.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] When a tester is active, the extension associates submitted bugs with the current testing session (see [Bug Management](../bugs/bug-management.md#testing-sessions)). This allows grouping all bugs found in a single testing pass.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
