[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Database Schema & Configuration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database Abstraction
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` — abstract database client interface  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/index.ts` — `getDatabase()` factory, returns the configured backend  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/schema.ts` — TypeScript type definitions for all database tables  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/postgres-schema.ts` — PostgreSQL-specific DDL and schema definitions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Backends
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### PostgreSQL (Production)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Configuration: `src/lib/db/postgres-config.ts`  
[CLAUDE] Client: `src/lib/db/postgres-client.ts`  
[CLAUDE] Bootstrap: `src/lib/db/postgres-bootstrap.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Connection settings come from environment variables (see `.env.example`). Default local values: `127.0.0.1:5432`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Worker architecture**: Some database operations run in a dedicated worker thread via `src/lib/db/postgres-worker.ts`. The worker is bundled separately by esbuild into `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs` at build time (`npm run build:db-worker`). `postgres-worker-bootstrap.mjs` initialises the worker context.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### In-Memory SQLite (Tests)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/local-test-database.ts` — SQLite-backed test database  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/local-test-database-runtime.ts` — runtime initialisation  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/test-database.ts` — test database factory  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/postgres-test-reset.ts` — resets PostgreSQL between test runs  
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/postgres-test-setup.test.ts` — test setup verification
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Selected via `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND=memory` (default for `npm test`) or `postgres`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Tables (inferred from service layer)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Table | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `users` | User accounts, `isAdmin` flag |
[CLAUDE] | `sessions` | Session tokens with expiry |
[CLAUDE] | `auth_action_tokens` | Password reset / email verification tokens |
[CLAUDE] | `organizations` | Workspace tenants |
[CLAUDE] | `organization_members` | User ↔ org membership |
[CLAUDE] | `organization_invitations` | Pending invitations |
[CLAUDE] | `projects` | Projects within an org |
[CLAUDE] | `project_sections` | Sections within a project |
[CLAUDE] | `project_members` | User ↔ project membership |
[CLAUDE] | `bugs` | Bug records |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_comments` | Comments on bugs |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_attachments` | Attachment metadata |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_history` | Change events per bug |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_data_jobs` | Import/export job records |
[CLAUDE] | `testing_sessions` | Tester sessions |
[CLAUDE] | `testing_session_logs` | Per-session activity log |
[CLAUDE] | `operational_logs` | Observability log entries |
[CLAUDE] | `operational_alerts` | Actionable alert records |
[CLAUDE] | `notifications` | Notification event records |
[CLAUDE] | `notification_deliveries` | Per-delivery status records |
[CLAUDE] | `api_keys` | Organization API keys |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Migrations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run with: `npm run db:migrate:postgres`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Script: `scripts/migrate-postgres.ts` — applies pending migrations against the configured PostgreSQL instance.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Type Definitions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/schema.ts` exports TypeScript types for all tables. `OperationalLogSeverity` is one example: `"debug" | "info" | "warn" | "error" | "critical"`. `OperationalAlertStatus` is `"open" | "acknowledged" | "resolved"`.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
