[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Local Development Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Prerequisites
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Node.js (LTS)
[CLAUDE] - npm
[CLAUDE] - Docker + Docker Compose
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## First-Time Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # 1. Clone and enter the repo
[CLAUDE] cd /Users/henrysmith/Empite/bug_tracker
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 2. Copy environment file
[CLAUDE] cp .env.example .env
[CLAUDE] # Keep default PostgreSQL settings unless you have a reason to change them
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 3. Install dependencies
[CLAUDE] npm install
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 4. Start PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 5. Run migrations
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 6. Start dev server
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 7. Open browser
[CLAUDE] open http://localhost:3000
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Daily Development
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Start PostgreSQL (if not running)
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Start dev server (predev builds the DB worker automatically)
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Environment Variables
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See `.env.example`. Required for full functionality:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Variable | Required | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `DATABASE_URL` or equivalent PG vars | Yes | Points to local PostgreSQL |
[CLAUDE] | `SENDGRID_API_KEY` | No | Only needed for email flow testing |
[CLAUDE] | `SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL` | No | Only needed for email flow testing |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Running Tests
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # Fast unit tests (in-memory SQLite, no Docker required)
[CLAUDE] npm test
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Unit tests against real PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] npm run test:unit:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # E2E tests (requires running app on port 3001)
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e:seed    # seed test DB first
[CLAUDE] npm run test:e2e
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Useful Commands
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run lint          # ESLint
[CLAUDE] npm run typecheck     # TypeScript check (slow — rebuilds from scratch)
[CLAUDE] npm run build         # Production build
[CLAUDE] npm run start         # Run production build locally
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Bootstrap
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] To create the first admin user on a fresh database, run the bootstrap script:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # See src/lib/db/bootstrap-admin.ts
[CLAUDE] npx tsx scripts/bootstrap-admin.ts   # (if script exists; otherwise adapt from bootstrap-admin.ts)
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Nginx / Domain / Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See:
[CLAUDE] - `docs/deployment-nginx.md` — reverse proxy and domain setup
[CLAUDE] - `docs/observability.md` — structured logging and file output
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
