[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/concepts/bug_tracker-domain-model.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: concept
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 5
[CLAUDE] tags: [domain-model, organizations, projects, bugs, multi-tenant]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Domain Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core Entities
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Organization
[CLAUDE]   └── Projects
[CLAUDE]         └── Sections
[CLAUDE]               └── Bugs
[CLAUDE]                     ├── Comments
[CLAUDE]                     ├── Attachments
[CLAUDE]                     └── History Events
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Organization
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The top-level tenant. Every user belongs to one or more organizations. All data (bugs, projects, notifications) is scoped to an organization. Users can switch between organizations they belong to.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Project
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A named collection of bugs within an organization. Projects have a `key` (short identifier), optional description, and an `isArchived` flag. Projects contain **Sections** for grouping bugs (e.g., "Frontend", "Backend", "Infrastructure").
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Bug
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The central entity. Fields:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Field | Type | Notes |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `title` | string | Short description |
[CLAUDE] | `description` | string | Full details |
[CLAUDE] | `severity` | enum | e.g. Low, Medium, High, Critical |
[CLAUDE] | `status` | enum | New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed |
[CLAUDE] | `reporterUserId` | int? | Who reported it |
[CLAUDE] | `assigneeUserId` | int? | Who is working on it |
[CLAUDE] | `projectId` | int | Which project |
[CLAUDE] | `sectionId` | int | Which section |
[CLAUDE] | `is_archived` | bool | Hidden from default views |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### User
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Users are members of organizations and optionally of specific projects. `isAdmin` is a boolean on the user record granting access to admin surfaces.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Relationships
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - User ↔ Organization: many-to-many via `organization_members`
[CLAUDE] - User ↔ Project: many-to-many via `project_members`
[CLAUDE] - Bug → Project → Organization: strict ownership chain
[CLAUDE] - Bug → Assignee (User): nullable FK
[CLAUDE] - Bug → Reporter (User): nullable FK
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Visibility Rules
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A user can see a bug if:
[CLAUDE] 1. They have an active organization session for the bug's organization, AND
[CLAUDE] 2. They are a member of the bug's project (or are an org admin)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The `requireActiveOrganizationSession()` guard enforces the organization boundary. Project membership is checked at the service layer.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Active Organization Session
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The "active organization" is the org currently selected by the user. It is stored in the session and resolved on each request. If a user belongs to multiple orgs, they must explicitly switch to see another org's data.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent Identity
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Agents (automated processes) interact via API key, not user sessions. They appear in bug history as agent actions rather than user actions. The `claimedBy` field on a bug records the agent identifier string.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/concepts/bug_tracker-bug-lifecycle.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: concept
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 4
[CLAUDE] tags: [bug-lifecycle, status, workflow, history]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Status Transitions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed
[CLAUDE]                                     ↑              ↓
[CLAUDE]                              (reopened)  →  In Progress
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs can be archived at any status. Archiving does not change status — it hides the bug from default list views. Pass `showArchived=true` to include archived bugs in queries.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Status Descriptions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Status | Meaning |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | New | Just submitted, not yet reviewed |
[CLAUDE] | Triaged | Reviewed, severity/priority confirmed, ready to assign |
[CLAUDE] | In Progress | Actively being worked on |
[CLAUDE] | Ready for QA | Fix complete, needs verification |
[CLAUDE] | Closed | Verified fixed or intentionally closed |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## History Tracking
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every state change, field edit, comment, and attachment action is recorded as a history event in `bug_history`. The timeline is available at `GET /api/bugs/[bugId]/history` (requires org admin).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] History event types follow the pattern `bug_<action>`, e.g.:
[CLAUDE] - `bug_created`
[CLAUDE] - `bug_status_changed`
[CLAUDE] - `bug_assigned`
[CLAUDE] - `bug_comment_added`
[CLAUDE] - `bug_import_created` — bug was created via CSV import
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The source of each event is determined by context:
[CLAUDE] - `bug_import_*` events → source is "Import"
[CLAUDE] - `bug_*` events → source is "User" (with actor ID)
[CLAUDE] - Other events → source is "System"
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Notification Triggers
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Notifications are sent on:
[CLAUDE] - Bug created (reporter gets confirmation; project members notified)
[CLAUDE] - Bug assigned (assignee notified)
[CLAUDE] - Bug status changed
[CLAUDE] - Bug closed / reopened
[CLAUDE] - Comment added
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent Workflow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Agents can participate in the lifecycle:
[CLAUDE] 1. `GET /api/agent/bugs` — find claimable bugs
[CLAUDE] 2. `POST /api/agent/bugs/[id]/claim` — claim a bug (sets `claimedBy`)
[CLAUDE] 3. `PATCH /api/agent/bugs/[id]/status` — update work state with a status note
[CLAUDE] 4. Agent closes/updates bug via the regular `PATCH /api/bugs/[id]` endpoint
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Agent actions appear in the history timeline with the agent identifier as actor.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bulk Operations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Multiple bugs can have their status updated simultaneously via `PATCH /api/bugs/bulk`. Requires an array of bug IDs and a target status. Useful for triage sessions closing multiple resolved issues at once.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Import Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs imported via CSV follow the same status model. The import service:
[CLAUDE] 1. Validates all rows
[CLAUDE] 2. Applies duplicate strategy (`skip_existing` or `update_existing`)
[CLAUDE] 3. Creates history events with `bug_import_*` types
[CLAUDE] 4. Returns a summary: created / updated / skipped / failed counts
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
