[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Tracker — System Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bug Tracker is a multi-tenant Next.js 16 application for capturing, triaging, and managing software issues inside authenticated workspaces.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Tech Stack
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Layer | Choice |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router, webpack mode) |
[CLAUDE] | Language | TypeScript 5 |
[CLAUDE] | UI | React 19, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui |
[CLAUDE] | Database | PostgreSQL (primary) + in-memory (test) |
[CLAUDE] | Email | SendGrid |
[CLAUDE] | Runtime | Node.js |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Top-Level Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] browser client
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ├── /app/(authenticated)/*   — protected workspace UI
[CLAUDE]     ├── /app/api/*               — Next.js Route Handlers (REST API)
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /auth/*          — login, signup, session, password flows
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /bugs/*          — CRUD, comments, attachments, bulk
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /agent/*         — agent automation API
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /extension/*     — Chrome extension API
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /admin/*         — admin surfaces (monitoring, alerts, users)
[CLAUDE]     │       ├── /organizations/* — org management, invitations
[CLAUDE]     │       └── /projects/*      — project and section management
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     └── /src/lib/*               — domain services, stores, utilities
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Major Subsystems
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Subsystem | Key files | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Auth | `src/lib/auth/` | Session cookies, email verification, password reset |
[CLAUDE] | Bugs | `src/lib/bugs/` | Core bug lifecycle, history, comments, attachments |
[CLAUDE] | Organizations | `src/lib/organizations/` | Multi-tenancy, invitations, billing, seats |
[CLAUDE] | Projects | `src/lib/projects/` | Projects and sections within an org |
[CLAUDE] | Monitoring | `src/lib/monitoring/` | Observability, operational logs, grouped errors, alerts |
[CLAUDE] | Notifications | `src/lib/notifications/` | Event-driven emails via SendGrid templates |
[CLAUDE] | Agent API | `src/lib/bugs/agent-api.ts` | Programmatic bug claiming and status updates for AI agents |
[CLAUDE] | MCP Server | `src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts` | Model Context Protocol server for LLM tool use |
[CLAUDE] | Extension | `src/lib/extension/` | Chrome extension version gating and auth |
[CLAUDE] | Data I/O | `src/lib/bugs/bug-data-*` | Bulk import/export with job tracking |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Request Flow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every API route is wrapped in `withRequestObservability(method, handler)` which records performance metrics, errors, and structured logs before delegating to the handler.
[CLAUDE] 
