[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 14
[CLAUDE] tags: [auth, session, password, email-verification]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Authentication System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Session Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Cookie-based sessions (`getSessionCookieName()`).
[CLAUDE] - Session token is stored in a cookie; expiry controlled by `getSessionMaxAgeSeconds()` / `getSessionExpirationDate()`.
[CLAUDE] - The session cookie is parsed manually from the `Cookie` header in Route Handlers — Next.js cookie helpers are not used directly.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Flows
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Flow | Entry point | Service |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Sign up | `POST /api/auth/signup` | `registerUserWithOrganization` |
[CLAUDE] | Login (web) | `POST /api/auth/login` | `authenticateUser` |
[CLAUDE] | Login (extension) | `POST /api/extension/auth/login` | `authenticateUser` |
[CLAUDE] | Logout | `POST /api/auth/logout` | `deleteSessionByToken` |
[CLAUDE] | Email verification | `POST /api/auth/verify-email` | `verifyEmailAddressFromTokenInDatabase` |
[CLAUDE] | Forgot password | `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` | `sendForgotPasswordNotificationFromDatabase` |
[CLAUDE] | Reset password | `POST /api/auth/reset-password` | `completePasswordResetFromTokenInDatabase` |
[CLAUDE] | Change password | `POST /api/auth/change-password` | `changeAuthenticatedUserPasswordInDatabase` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Functions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `requireAuthenticatedUser(request)` — throws `AuthenticationError` if no valid session; used in user-facing routes.
[CLAUDE] - `requireAdminUser(request)` — additionally checks for admin role; used in all `/api/admin/*` routes.
[CLAUDE] - `requireAgentApiUser(request)` — validates agent API key; used in `/api/agent/*`.
[CLAUDE] - `requireExtensionAuthenticatedUser(request)` — reads auth from `Authorization: Bearer` header; used in extension routes.
[CLAUDE] - `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest(request)` — non-throwing session read.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Token Store
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Short-lived action tokens (email verification, password reset) live in `src/lib/auth/auth-action-token-store.ts` and are separate from session tokens stored in `auth-user-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Signup Side Effects
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] On successful signup, `sendSignupNotificationsFromDatabase` fires the welcome email and email-verification email.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/bug-lifecycle.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 12
[CLAUDE] tags: [bugs, lifecycle, history, comments, attachments]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Statuses
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs move through these states (defined in `all-bugs-filters.ts`):
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs can also be **archived** (`is_archived` flag) independently of status.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core Operations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Operation | API | Service function |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Create | `POST /api/bugs` | `createBug` |
[CLAUDE] | Read | `GET /api/bugs/:bugId` | `getBugById` |
[CLAUDE] | Update | `PATCH /api/bugs/:bugId` | `updateBug` |
[CLAUDE] | List | `GET /api/bugs` | `listBugs` |
[CLAUDE] | Bulk status update | `PATCH /api/bugs/bulk` | `bulkUpdateBugs` |
[CLAUDE] | Add comment | `POST /api/bugs/:bugId/comments` | `createBugComment` |
[CLAUDE] | List comments | `GET /api/bugs/:bugId/comments` | `listBugCommentsForBug` |
[CLAUDE] | Add attachment | `POST /api/bugs/:bugId/attachments` | `createBugAttachment` |
[CLAUDE] | Download attachment | `GET /api/bugs/:bugId/attachments/:id` | `getAttachmentForBug` |
[CLAUDE] | Delete attachment | `DELETE /api/bugs/:bugId/attachments/:id` | `deleteBugAttachment` |
[CLAUDE] | View history | `GET /api/bugs/:bugId/history` | `listBugHistoryTimelineEntries` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## History Tracking
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every mutation records a `BugHistoryTimelineEntry` via `bug-history-service.ts`. Entries carry `eventType`, `changedFields` (with `previousValue` / `nextValue`), and a source classification (user action vs. import vs. system).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Helper `getBugHistoryEntrySource` in `bug-history.helpers.ts` classifies entries:
[CLAUDE] - `bug_import_*` events → "Import"
[CLAUDE] - `bug_*` events → user name
[CLAUDE] - everything else → "System"
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Filtering & Sorting
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `AllBugsFilterState` (in `all-bugs-filters.ts`) controls the list view:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Filter by: `projectId`, `status`, `reporterUserId`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `showArchived`
[CLAUDE] - Sort by: `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `status`, `project` (asc/desc)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `buildAllBugSearchParams` validates then serialises the filter state into `URLSearchParams`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Severity
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Severity badges rendered by `components/bugs/severity-badge.tsx`. Values defined by the bug service (not enumerated in the truncated source, but used in API body validation as strings).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Attachments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Files stored via `attachmentStorage` (`src/lib/storage/attachment-storage.ts`). Served through the authenticated attachment route; access requires an active organization session and ownership verification.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
