[CLAUDE] source_count: 8
[CLAUDE] tags: [agent, automation, mcp, api]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Agent API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The agent API (`/api/agent/*`) exposes a stable interface for AI agents and automated tooling to interact with bugs without a browser session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Authentication
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Agent requests use an API key rather than a session cookie. `requireAgentApiUser` in `agent-api.ts` validates the key and resolves the acting user identity.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Endpoints
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `GET` | `/api/agent/bugs` | List claimable bugs (`listClaimableBugs`) |
[CLAUDE] | `GET` | `/api/agent/bugs/:bugId` | Get full bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | `POST` | `/api/agent/bugs/:bugId/claim` | Claim a bug for an agent (`claimedBy` string) |
[CLAUDE] | `PATCH` | `/api/agent/bugs/:bugId/status` | Update agent work state, optionally set `statusNote` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Response Helpers
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `agent-api.ts` exports:
[CLAUDE] - `createAgentApiSuccessResponse(data)` — standardised success envelope
[CLAUDE] - `createAgentApiErrorResponse(message, status)` — standardised error envelope
[CLAUDE] - `handleAgentApiError(error)` — maps known error types to HTTP responses
[CLAUDE] - `parseAgentBugId(value)` — validates bug ID from path params (returns `null` on invalid)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## CLI & Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/bugs/agent-cli.ts` — command-line interface over the agent API, invoked via `npm run bugs:cli`
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/bugs/agent-integration.ts` — higher-level orchestration helpers for agent workflows
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts` — MCP server exposing bug operations as LLM tools, invoked via `npm run mcp:server`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Scripts
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Script | Entry |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `npm run bugs:cli` | `scripts/bug-agent-cli.ts` |
[CLAUDE] | `npm run mcp:server` | `scripts/mcp-server.ts` |
[CLAUDE] | `npm run alerts:cli` | `scripts/alerts-cli.ts` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Ralph Agent
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `scripts/ralph/` contains a self-contained sub-agent with its own `prompt.md`, `project-context.md`, and shell runner `ralph.sh`. Ralph appears to be an internal QA/bug-intake agent.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
