[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/monitoring.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 18
[CLAUDE] tags: [monitoring, observability, alerts, logging, performance]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Monitoring & Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Request Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All API routes are wrapped with `withRequestObservability(method, handler)` from `src/lib/monitoring/request-observability.ts`. This middleware captures:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - HTTP method, route, status code
[CLAUDE] - Response time
[CLAUDE] - Errors and their fingerprints
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Structured events are written via `observability-logger-service.ts` to the operational log store and optionally to `observability-file-sink.ts` (NDJSON at `log/observability.ndjson`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Operational Logs
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/monitoring/operational-log-store.ts` persists structured log entries. Severity levels: `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`, `critical`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API: `GET /api/admin/logs` (paginated, filterable by severity).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Error Grouping
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/monitoring/error-fingerprint.ts` computes a deterministic fingerprint per error (stack, message, route). `grouped-errors-service.ts` aggregates log entries by fingerprint into error groups.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API: `GET /api/admin/errors` (filtered to `error`/`critical` severity by default).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Operational Alerts
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/monitoring/operational-alert-store.ts` and `operational-alert-service.ts` manage discrete alerts with severity and status. Alerts can be promoted to bugs via `createBugFromOperationalAlert`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API:
[CLAUDE] - `GET /api/admin/alerts` — list with filters (severity, status, source, date range)
[CLAUDE] - `GET /api/admin/alerts/:alertId` — detail
[CLAUDE] - `PATCH /api/admin/alerts/:alertId` — update status
[CLAUDE] - `POST /api/admin/alerts/:alertId/bugs` — create bug from alert
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] CLI: `npm run alerts:cli` → `operational-alert-cli.ts`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Performance Tracking
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/monitoring/performance.ts` records timing samples. `endpoint-performance-service.ts` aggregates by endpoint over configurable windows.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API: `GET /api/admin/performance/endpoints`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Page Load Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Client-side page load events are recorded via `components/app/page-load-observability.tsx` and sent to `POST /api/observability/page-load`. Server-side processing in `page-load-observability.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organisation Usage
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `org-usage-service.ts` computes per-org usage statistics.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API: `GET /api/admin/performance/org-usage`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Dashboard Summary
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `dashboard-summary-service.ts` aggregates key metrics into a single summary payload.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin API: `GET /api/admin/dashboard/summary`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Data Redaction
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `observability-redaction.ts` strips sensitive fields (passwords, tokens) before log events are persisted.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
