[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 5
[CLAUDE] tags: [extension, chrome, browser]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Chrome Extension
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The browser extension allows users to report bugs directly from any web page without leaving the browser. Source lives in `extension/` at the repo root.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `extension/manifest.json` | Chrome extension manifest |
[CLAUDE] | `extension/popup.html` | Extension popup UI |
[CLAUDE] | `extension/popup.js` | Popup logic (auth, bug submission) |
[CLAUDE] | `extension/popup.css` | Popup styles |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Separate API routes prefixed `/api/extension/` provide:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Endpoint | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/auth/login` | Authenticate and return a bearer token |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/auth/logout` | Invalidate the extension session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/auth/session` | Validate existing session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/projects` | List projects available to the user |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/bugs` | Create a bug with evidence |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/bugs/:bugId/evidence` | Attach screenshot/recording to existing bug during a testing session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/version` | Current supported extension version |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Extension auth uses `Authorization: Bearer <token>` headers (not cookies).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] When the extension is active during a QA session, `requireActiveBugTestingSession` gates evidence uploads. The testing session model (`testing-session-*.ts`) tracks active QA sessions per user.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Version Gating
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `extension-version.ts` compares the extension's reported version against the server's minimum supported version. Outdated extensions receive a version-mismatch response.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Install Prompt
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `app/(authenticated)/dashboard/extension-install-panel.tsx` surfaces an install CTA to users who have not yet installed the extension.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
