[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Organizations & Multi-Tenancy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every authenticated user belongs to one or more **organizations**. Within an organization, users are members with roles. Projects and bugs are scoped to an organization.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The active organization for a request is resolved by `active-organization-service.ts` and stored in the session via `active-organization-session.ts`. All authenticated API routes call `requireActiveOrganizationSession` to enforce this scope.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Invitation Flow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. Admin sends invitation → `organization-invitation-service.ts` creates a pending invitation and fires an email via `organization-invitation-email-service.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 2. Invitee lands on `/invitations/:invitationId` — `invitation-landing-content.ts` validates the token and describes the invitation.
[CLAUDE] 3. Invitee accepts via `invitation-activation-form.tsx` → `POST /api/invitations/activate` → `organization-invitation-activation-service.ts` converts the invitation to membership.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Membership & Access
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `organization-membership-service.ts` — add/remove/query members
[CLAUDE] - `organization-access-service.ts` — role checks; `requireOrganizationAdminAccessForUser` used for admin-gated history/audit routes
[CLAUDE] - `project-membership-service.ts` — per-project access within an org
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Seats & Billing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `organization-seat-service.ts` — tracks occupied seats vs. plan limit
[CLAUDE] - `organization-billing-service.ts` — billing state and plan information
[CLAUDE] - `billing-ui.ts` — client-side billing display helpers
[CLAUDE] - UI: `app/(authenticated)/billing/organization-billing-panel.tsx`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Audit Log
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `organization-audit-log-service.ts` / `organization-audit-log-store.ts` record significant org-level events. Accessible at `/organization/audit`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Onboarding
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] New users create their first organization via `POST /api/onboarding/organizations` after signup.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organization Switcher
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `components/app/organization-switcher.tsx` allows switching the active org without logging out. The active org is persisted to session server-side.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
