[CLAUDE] type: runbook
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 2
[CLAUDE] tags: [deployment, nginx, production]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Deployment
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Production Build
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run build        # Next.js build + esbuild postgres-worker
[CLAUDE] npm run start        # Start production server
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The `build` script also compiles the PostgreSQL worker to `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Nginx / Reverse Proxy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Full reverse-proxy and domain setup is documented in `docs/deployment-nginx.md` in the repository. This covers:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Nginx configuration for the Next.js server
[CLAUDE] - Domain and SSL setup
[CLAUDE] - Port forwarding
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Observability in Production
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Structured logs are written to `log/observability.ndjson` (NDJSON format) via `observability-file-sink.ts`. See `docs/observability.md` for log rotation, monitoring integration, and alerting setup.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Database
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Run migrations against the production database before deploying a new version:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] NODE_ENV=production npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Ensure `DATABASE_URL` (or `POSTGRES_*` vars) points to the production instance.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Bootstrap
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] On first deployment, `bootstrap-admin.ts` seeds the initial admin account from environment variables. Run once after the first migration.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## run.sh
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `run.sh` in the repo root is a convenience wrapper for production start. Review its contents before use in a new environment.
