[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 14
[CLAUDE] tags: [auth, session, password, email-verification]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Authentication System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Session Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sessions are stored in PostgreSQL via `auth-user-store.ts`. A session cookie is set on login/signup and cleared on logout.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Key helpers in `src/lib/auth/session.ts`:
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionCookieName()` — returns the cookie name
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionExpirationDate()` — absolute expiry date
[CLAUDE] - `getSessionMaxAgeSeconds()` — max-age for Set-Cookie
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest(request)` — reads session from standard cookie header (browser flows).  
[CLAUDE] `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest(request)` — reads session from `Authorization` header (extension flows).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Flows
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Login
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/login` — validates credentials, creates session, sets cookie.  
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/extension/auth/login` — same but returns token in JSON body for the extension.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Signup
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/signup` — registers user + organization in one step, fires welcome/verification emails via `auth-notification-service.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Email Verification
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/verify-email` — consumes a token from `auth-action-token-store.ts` to verify the email address.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Password Flows
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` → sends reset email  
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/reset-password` → completes reset with token  
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/change-password` → changes password for authenticated user
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Logout
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/logout` — deletes session from DB, clears cookie.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Guards
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `requireAuthenticatedUser(request)` — throws `AuthenticationError` if no valid session
[CLAUDE] - `requireAdminUser(request)` — throws `AuthenticationError` if not admin
[CLAUDE] - `requireExtensionAuthenticatedUser(request)` — for extension routes
[CLAUDE] - `requireActiveOrganizationSession(request)` — ensures user has an active org context; throws `ActiveOrganizationSessionError`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Error Types
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `AuthenticationError` — unauthenticated or unauthorized  
[CLAUDE] `ChangePasswordServiceError`, `ForgotPasswordServiceError`, `ResetPasswordServiceError`, `EmailVerificationServiceError` — domain-specific errors thrown by respective services
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
