[CLAUDE] source_count: 12
[CLAUDE] tags: [bugs, lifecycle, status, severity, filters]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Statuses
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs move through these statuses (defined in `all-bugs-filters.ts`):
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs can also be archived (`is_archived`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Severity Levels
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Rendered via `severity-badge.tsx`. Levels come from the `severity` field on the bug record.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Core API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Route | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs` | List bugs with filters |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs` | Create a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Update bug fields |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/bulk` | Bulk status update |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | List comments |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | Add comment |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments` | Upload attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Download attachment |
[CLAUDE] | DELETE | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Delete attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/history` | Audit timeline |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Filtering (`all-bugs-filters.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Filter state fields: `projectId`, `status`, `reporterUserId`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `showArchived`, `sortField`, `sortDirection`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sort fields: `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `status`, `project`.  
[CLAUDE] Sort directions: `asc`, `desc` (default: `createdAt desc`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `buildAllBugSearchParams(filters)` serializes a filter state into `URLSearchParams` after validation.  
[CLAUDE] `validateAllBugFilters(filters)` throws on invalid values (bad dates, bad IDs, unknown sort fields).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug History
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/bug-history-service.ts` tracks field-level changes. Each `BugHistoryTimelineEntry` has:
[CLAUDE] - `eventType` — e.g. `bug_created`, `bug_status_changed`, `bug_import_*`
[CLAUDE] - `changedFields` — array of `{ previousValue, nextValue }`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `getBugHistoryEntrySource(entry)` classifies source as "Import", "User", or "System".
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Comments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/bug-comment-service.ts` and `bug-comment-store.ts`. Comments have `body` and optional `visibility`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Attachments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/attachment-store.ts` + `attachment-storage.ts`. Files stored via `attachmentStorage` abstraction (local path in dev).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Data Import / Export
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin-only. Jobs tracked in `bug-data-job-store.ts` with statuses: `queued`, `running`, `completed`, `completed_with_warnings`, `failed`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Import supports `skip_existing` and `update_existing` duplicate strategies.  
[CLAUDE] Export produces a manifest with `bugCount`, `historyEntryCount`, `attachmentCount`, `missingFileCount`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/testing-session-service.ts` — QA testing sessions attach evidence (screenshots, logs) to bugs via `POST /api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence`.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
