[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Chrome Extension API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The browser extension (`extension/`) allows users to report bugs directly from any web page.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] extension/
[CLAUDE]   manifest.json   — Chrome extension manifest
[CLAUDE]   popup.html      — extension popup UI
[CLAUDE]   popup.css       — popup styles
[CLAUDE]   popup.js        — popup logic
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension API Routes
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All under `/api/extension/`:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Route | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/auth/login` | Login with email/password, returns token in JSON |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/auth/logout` | Invalidate extension session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/auth/session` | Check current session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/projects` | List projects for bug assignment |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/bugs` | Submit a bug from extension |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` | Attach evidence to a bug during a testing session |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/extension/version` | Extension version info |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Difference
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Extension uses `Authorization` header (Bearer token) instead of a session cookie. `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest()` reads from this header.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Session Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `requireActiveBugTestingSession()` — extension evidence uploads are gated on an active QA testing session for the bug.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Version Management
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/extension/extension-version.ts` + `extension-service.ts` — tracks compatible extension versions.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Install UI
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `/chrome-extension` page and `/dashboard` → `extension-install-panel.tsx` guide users through installation.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
