[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Database
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Backends
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Backend | When used |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | PostgreSQL | Production and `npm run test:unit:postgres` |
[CLAUDE] | In-memory (SQLite-compatible) | Default unit tests (`npm test`) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Controlled by `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND` env var.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | File | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/schema.ts` | Shared schema types (used by both backends) |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-schema.ts` | PostgreSQL DDL definitions |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-client.ts` | PostgreSQL connection pool (uses `pg`) |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-config.ts` | Config from env vars |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` | Abstraction layer returned by `getDatabase()` |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/index.ts` | `getDatabase()` export |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-worker.ts` | Worker thread for CPU-bound DB operations |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/bootstrap-admin.ts` | Seeds initial admin user |
[CLAUDE] | `src/lib/db/postgres-bootstrap.ts` | Creates schema if not exists |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Worker Pattern
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `postgres-worker.ts` runs in a Node.js worker thread (built to `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs` by `build:db-worker`). The `predev` script builds it before `next dev` starts.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Migrations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Runs `scripts/migrate-postgres.ts` with env loaded from `.env`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Schema Types (from `schema.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `OperationalLogSeverity` — `"debug" | "info" | "warn" | "error" | "critical"`
[CLAUDE] - `OperationalAlertStatus` — alert lifecycle states
[CLAUDE] - Bug job statuses — `"queued" | "running" | "completed" | "completed_with_warnings" | "failed"`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Local Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Requires Docker. Run:
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Default connection: `127.0.0.1:5432`. See `.env.example` for full config.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Test Database
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `local-test-database.ts` + `local-test-database-runtime.ts` — in-memory database for fast unit tests, no Docker needed.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `postgres-test-reset.ts` — resets schema between postgres test runs.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
