[CLAUDE] # Organizations & Multi-Tenancy
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Organization
[CLAUDE]   └── Members (users with roles)
[CLAUDE]   └── Projects
[CLAUDE]         └── Sections
[CLAUDE]         └── Bugs
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every authenticated action operates within an active organization context, resolved via `requireActiveOrganizationSession()` (stored in `active-organization-session.ts`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Services
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Service | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `organization-service.ts` | Create/read organizations |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-membership-service.ts` | Add/remove/list members |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-access-service.ts` | Role-based access checks; `requireOrganizationAdminAccessForUser()` |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-invitation-service.ts` | Create and validate invitations |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-invitation-activation-service.ts` | Accept invitation and join org |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-invitation-email-service.ts` | Send invitation emails |
[CLAUDE] | `active-organization-service.ts` | Get/set user's active org |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-seat-service.ts` | Seat limit enforcement |
[CLAUDE] | `organization-billing-service.ts` | Billing state per org |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Invitation Flow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. Admin creates invitation → `POST /api/organizations/invitations`
[CLAUDE] 2. Invitee receives email with token
[CLAUDE] 3. Invitee visits `/invitations/[invitationId]`
[CLAUDE] 4. `POST /api/invitations/activate` — activates invitation and creates membership
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Billing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `billing-ui.ts` — billing state helpers for the UI.  
[CLAUDE] `organization-billing-panel.tsx` — billing management page at `/billing`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Org Switcher
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `organization-switcher.tsx` — UI component for switching active organization. Active org persisted in session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Audit Log
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/audit/organization-audit-log-service.ts` + `organization-audit-log-store.ts` — records admin-level actions within an org.  
[CLAUDE] Accessible at `/organization/audit`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Access Context
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `project-access-context.ts` — generates messaging for users who lack project access.
