[CLAUDE] # Local Development Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Prerequisites
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Node.js + npm
[CLAUDE] - Docker + Docker Compose
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## First-Time Setup
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] # 1. Clone and enter repo
[CLAUDE] cd /path/to/bug_tracker
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 2. Create env file
[CLAUDE] cp .env.example .env
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 3. Install dependencies
[CLAUDE] npm install
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 4. Start PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 5. Run migrations
[CLAUDE] npm run db:migrate:postgres
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # 6. Start dev server
[CLAUDE] npm run dev
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Open `http://localhost:3000`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Daily Workflow
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] docker compose up -d postgres   # ensure DB is running
[CLAUDE] npm run dev                     # start Next.js dev server
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Environment Variables
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `.env.example` contains all required vars with local defaults. Key vars:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Var | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `DATABASE_URL` (or similar) | PostgreSQL connection string |
[CLAUDE] | `SENDGRID_API_KEY` | Leave empty to disable email in dev |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Test Commands
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```bash
[CLAUDE] npm test                    # fast unit tests (in-memory DB, no Docker needed)
