[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Observability Operations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] > Detailed setup in `docs/observability.md` in the repository.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Log File
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Structured NDJSON logs are written to `log/observability.ndjson` by `observability-file-sink.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Each line is a JSON event with fields including severity, timestamp, and request metadata.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Viewing Logs (Admin UI)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `/admin/monitoring` → Logs tab — paginated log viewer with severity filter.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Viewing Errors (Admin UI)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `/admin/monitoring` → Errors tab — grouped errors by fingerprint. Click an error group to view individual entries or link to a bug.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Viewing Alerts (Admin UI)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `/admin/monitoring` → Alerts tab — operational alerts with filter state (`severity`, `status`, `source`, date range, `limit`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alert actions:
[CLAUDE] - Update status (`PATCH /api/admin/alerts/[id]`)
[CLAUDE] - Create bug from alert (`POST /api/admin/alerts/[id]/bugs`)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Performance Dashboard
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `/admin/monitoring` → Performance tab — endpoint latency by window, org usage stats.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Sensitive Data
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `observability-redaction.ts` strips sensitive fields before any log is persisted or transmitted. Do not bypass this layer when adding new log events.
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
