[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 12
[CLAUDE] tags: [auth, session, password, email-verification, jwt]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Authentication System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Session Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sessions are cookie-based. The cookie name and expiry are controlled by `src/lib/auth/session.ts` (`getSessionCookieName`, `getSessionExpirationDate`, `getSessionMaxAgeSeconds`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] On login (`POST /api/auth/login`), the server sets an HTTP-only session cookie. On logout (`POST /api/auth/logout`), the token is deleted from the database and the cookie is cleared.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Two session extraction helpers exist:
[CLAUDE] - `getAuthenticatedSessionFromRequest` — reads the session cookie (browser app)
[CLAUDE] - `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest` — reads from request headers (Chrome extension)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Service Guards
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All protected API routes call one of:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Guard | File | Use |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `requireAuthenticatedUser` | `auth-service.ts` | Any logged-in user |
[CLAUDE] | `requireAdminUser` | `auth-service.ts` | Admin-only routes |
[CLAUDE] | `requireAgentApiUser` | `agent-api.ts` | Agent API key auth |
[CLAUDE] | `requireExtensionAuthenticatedUser` | `auth-service.ts` | Extension header auth |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] These throw `AuthenticationError` on failure; API routes catch this and return 401.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Auth Flows
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Signup
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/signup` → `registerUserWithOrganization` → `sendSignupNotificationsFromDatabase`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Creates the user, creates their organization, sets session cookie, fires welcome + verification emails.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Email Verification
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/verify-email` → `verifyEmailAddressFromTokenInDatabase`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Token-based; token stored in `auth-action-token-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Forgot Password
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` → `sendForgotPasswordNotificationFromDatabase`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Always returns 200 to avoid email enumeration.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Reset Password
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/reset-password` → `completePasswordResetFromTokenInDatabase`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Validates token from `auth-action-token-store`, hashes and updates password via `reset-password-service.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Change Password
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/auth/change-password` → `changeAuthenticatedUserPasswordInDatabase`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Requires current password; uses `change-password-service.ts`. Sends notification email on success.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Password Hashing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/auth/password.ts` — utility for hashing and comparing passwords.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Related Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] src/lib/auth/
[CLAUDE] ├── auth-service.ts              — core auth logic, session guards
[CLAUDE] ├── auth-user-store.ts           — user DB queries
[CLAUDE] ├── auth-action-token-store.ts   — email action tokens (verify, reset)
[CLAUDE] ├── auth-notification-service.ts — signup/change-password emails
[CLAUDE] ├── session.ts                   — cookie name/expiry config
[CLAUDE] ├── password.ts                  — hash + compare
[CLAUDE] ├── email-verification-service.ts
[CLAUDE] ├── forgot-password-service.ts
[CLAUDE] ├── reset-password-service.ts
[CLAUDE] └── change-password-service.ts
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
