[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Management System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug Lifecycle
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs move through statuses: `New → Triaged → In Progress → Ready for QA → Closed`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bugs belong to a **project** and optionally a **section** within that project. They can be archived without closing.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## API Surface
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs` | List bugs (filter by project, status, reporter, date range, sort) |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs` | Create bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/[bugId]` | Update bug fields |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/bugs/bulk` | Bulk status update |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | List comments |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/comments` | Add comment |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments` | Upload attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Download attachment |
[CLAUDE] | DELETE | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/attachments/[id]` | Delete attachment |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/bugs/[bugId]/history` | Bug change history (admin only) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Filter State
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/app/(authenticated)/bugs/all-bugs-filters.ts` manages client-side filter state and URL serialization.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Sort fields: `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `status`, `project`.  
[CLAUDE] Sort directions: `asc`, `desc` (default: `desc` by `createdAt`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Filter validation throws descriptive errors surfaced in the UI before any API call.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Bug History
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every mutation to a bug is recorded as a timeline entry in `bug-history-store.ts`. Each entry captures:
[CLAUDE] - `eventType` (e.g. `bug_created`, `bug_status_changed`, `bug_import_created`)
[CLAUDE] - `changedFields` — array of `{ field, previousValue, nextValue }`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Helper `getBugHistoryEntrySource` distinguishes user edits, import operations, and system events.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Attachments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Files are stored via `attachmentStorage` (`src/lib/storage/attachment-storage.ts`). The store layer (`attachment-store.ts`) records metadata. Retrieval streams the file from disk.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Comments
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Comments have a `visibility` field (public/internal). Both the comment list and creation require an active organization session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Data Import / Export
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Managed as async jobs tracked in `bug-data-job-store.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Import flow**: validate CSV → create job → run import → record created/updated/skipped/failed counts  
[CLAUDE] **Export flow**: create job → serialize bugs + history + attachments → write zip → record manifest
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Job statuses: `queued → running → completed | completed_with_warnings | failed`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Duplicate strategies on import: `skip_existing` or `update_existing`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] See type definitions in `src/app/(authenticated)/admin/bug-data/bug-data-management-panel.helpers.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Key Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] src/lib/bugs/
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-service.ts               — core CRUD, list, bulk update
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-comment-service.ts       — comment creation and listing
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-history-service.ts       — timeline generation
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-data-import-service.ts   — CSV import logic
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-data-export-service.ts   — export/zip generation
[CLAUDE] ├── bug-data-job-store.ts        — async job tracking
[CLAUDE] ├── attachment-store.ts          — attachment metadata
[CLAUDE] └── errors.ts                    — BugServiceError
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/organizations.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 10
[CLAUDE] tags: [organizations, projects, multi-tenant, invitations, billing]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Organizations & Projects
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Multi-Tenancy Model
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app is multi-tenant at the organization level. Each user belongs to one or more organizations. All data (bugs, projects, notifications) is scoped to an organization.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The active organization for a request is resolved via `requireActiveOrganizationSession` (`src/lib/organizations/active-organization-session.ts`), which reads a stored active-org preference from the session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Users can switch organizations via the `OrganizationSwitcher` component.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Organization Membership
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Users are members of organizations with a role.
[CLAUDE] - `organization-membership-service.ts` handles adding/removing members.
[CLAUDE] - `organization-access-service.ts` exposes `requireOrganizationAdminAccessForUser` for admin-gated operations.
[CLAUDE] - `organization-seat-service.ts` enforces seat limits tied to billing plan.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Invitations
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. Admin sends invite → `organization-invitation-service.ts` creates a record + `organization-invitation-email-service.ts` sends email.
[CLAUDE] 2. Invitee lands on `/invitations/[invitationId]` → sees invitation landing page.
[CLAUDE] 3. Invitee activates → `organization-invitation-activation-service.ts` creates/links their account.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Token is embedded in the invitation URL. Logic in `src/app/invitations/[invitationId]/invitation-landing-content.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Projects
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Projects are created by admins and scoped to an organization. Each project can have **sections** (ordered groupings of bugs).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | API | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/admin/projects` | List all projects |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/admin/projects` | Create project |
[CLAUDE] | `PATCH /api/admin/projects/[id]` | Update (name, key, description, archive) |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/admin/projects/[id]/sections` | List sections |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/admin/projects/[id]/sections` | Create section |
[CLAUDE] | `PATCH /api/admin/projects/[id]/sections/[sid]` | Update section (name, order, archive) |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Project access for non-admin users is controlled by `project-membership-service.ts`. The context helper `src/app/(authenticated)/project-access-context.ts` generates UI copy for unauthorized states.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Billing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `organization-billing-service.ts` manages subscription state. `billing-ui.ts` drives UI visibility rules based on plan. Seat enforcement happens in `organization-seat-service.ts` before invitations are accepted.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
