[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Notification System
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Architecture
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] Bug Event
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ▼
[CLAUDE] bug-notification-event-service.ts   — creates a notification event record
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ▼
[CLAUDE] bug-recipient-service.ts            — resolves who should receive this event
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ▼
[CLAUDE] notification-dispatcher.ts          — dispatches to delivery channels
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ▼
[CLAUDE] sendgrid-delivery.ts                — sends via SendGrid API
[CLAUDE]     │
[CLAUDE]     ▼
[CLAUDE] notification-store.ts               — records delivery attempt + status
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Event Types
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Bug lifecycle events that trigger notifications:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Bug created | `bug-created.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug assigned | `bug-assigned.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug status changed | `bug-status-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug closed | `bug-closed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Bug reopened | `bug-reopened.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Comment added | `bug-comment.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Auth events:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Event | Template |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Signup | `welcome.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Email verification | `verification.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Forgot password | `forgot-password.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password reset complete | `password-reset-complete.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Password changed | `password-changed.html` |
[CLAUDE] | Org invitation | `organization-invitation.html` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Template Engine
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `template-engine.ts` renders HTML templates in `src/lib/notifications/templates/`. All templates extend `base-layout.html`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `email-template-registry.ts` maps event types to their template files and subject lines.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Admin Controls
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admins can:
[CLAUDE] - View delivery history: `GET /api/admin/notifications/deliveries`
[CLAUDE] - Retry a failed delivery: `POST /api/admin/notifications/deliveries/[id]/retry`
[CLAUDE] - View/update notification settings (which events send to which recipient groups): `GET|PATCH /api/admin/notifications/settings`
[CLAUDE] - Retry a failed event: `POST /api/admin/notifications/events/[id]/retry`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Configuration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] SendGrid API key is set via environment variable. Leave empty for local dev unless testing email flows.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/monitoring.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 12
[CLAUDE] tags: [monitoring, observability, alerts, performance, logging]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Monitoring & Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Request Observability
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Every API route is wrapped with `withRequestObservability(method, handler)` from `src/lib/monitoring/request-observability.ts`. This middleware records:
[CLAUDE] - HTTP method, path, status code
[CLAUDE] - Duration
[CLAUDE] - Errors (with fingerprint for grouping)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Output goes to `operational-log-store.ts` (DB) and optionally `observability-file-sink.ts` (NDJSON file at `log/observability.ndjson`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Page load events are tracked via `page-load-observability.ts` and the `PageLoadObservability` component, reported to `POST /api/observability/page-load`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Operational Logs
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin endpoint: `GET /api/admin/logs`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Queryable by severity: `debug | info | warn | error | critical`  
[CLAUDE] Results are paginated (`PaginatedLogQueryOptions`).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Error Grouping
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Errors are fingerprinted via `error-fingerprint.ts` and grouped by `grouped-errors-service.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin endpoints:
[CLAUDE] - `GET /api/admin/errors` — grouped error summary (severity filter: `error | critical`)
[CLAUDE] - `PATCH /api/admin/errors/[fingerprint]/bug` — link an error group to an existing bug
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Operational Alerts
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alerts are raised when monitored conditions breach thresholds.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | API | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/admin/alerts` | List alerts (filter by severity, status, source, date range, limit) |
[CLAUDE] | `GET /api/admin/alerts/[id]` | Alert detail |
[CLAUDE] | `PATCH /api/admin/alerts/[id]` | Update alert status |
[CLAUDE] | `POST /api/admin/alerts/[id]/bugs` | Create a bug from an alert |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Alert statuses and the alert CLI are implemented in `operational-alert-service.ts` and `operational-alert-cli.ts`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Performance Tracking
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **Endpoint performance**: `GET /api/admin/performance/endpoints` — latency by endpoint over a configurable window
[CLAUDE] - **Org usage stats**: `GET /api/admin/performance/org-usage` — per-organization usage metrics
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Both call services in `src/lib/monitoring/`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Dashboard Summary
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `GET /api/admin/dashboard/summary` returns aggregated counts (bugs, alerts, errors) for the admin dashboard home.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Data Redaction
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `observability-redaction.ts` strips sensitive fields (passwords, tokens) from log payloads before persistence.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/agent-integration.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 6
[CLAUDE] tags: [agent, mcp, cli, automation, coordination]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Agent Integration
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The bug tracker exposes three agent interfaces:
[CLAUDE] 1. **REST Agent API** — HTTP endpoints under `/api/agent/`
[CLAUDE] 2. **Agent CLI** — `npm run bugs:cli` (scripts via `tsx scripts/bug-agent-cli.ts`)
[CLAUDE] 3. **MCP Server** — `npm run mcp:server` (Model Context Protocol for LLM tooling)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent REST API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] All agent routes use `requireAgentApiUser` for authentication (API key, not session cookie).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs` | List claimable (unassigned, open) bugs |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]` | Get bug detail |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` | Claim a bug (set `claimedBy`) |
[CLAUDE] | PATCH | `/api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/status` | Update agent work state + status note |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Claim Request Body
[CLAUDE] ```json
[CLAUDE] { "claimedBy": "agent-name" }
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ### Status Update Body
[CLAUDE] ```json
[CLAUDE] {
[CLAUDE]   "claimedBy": "agent-name",
[CLAUDE]   "state": "in_progress | completed | ...",
[CLAUDE]   "statusNote": "optional string"
[CLAUDE] }
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Helper functions in `src/lib/bugs/agent-api.ts`:
[CLAUDE] - `parseAgentBugId` — validates and parses bug ID from route params
[CLAUDE] - `createAgentApiSuccessResponse` / `createAgentApiErrorResponse`
[CLAUDE] - `handleAgentApiError` — maps service errors to HTTP responses
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent CLI
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/agent-cli.ts` implements a CLI mode for scripted agent workflows (fetch, claim, update bugs from terminal). Run via `npm run bugs:cli`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## MCP Server
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/mcp-server.ts` exposes bug tracker operations as MCP tools, enabling LLM clients that speak the Model Context Protocol to interact with bugs directly. Run via `npm run mcp:server`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Multi-Agent Coordination
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] From raw source notes (`shared/agent_bugtracker copy.md`):
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] > Agent should be automated and if multiple agents working on this it should coordinate with others how to perform its task.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The claim mechanism (`POST /api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` with `claimedBy`) is the primary coordination primitive — agents claim bugs before working on them to prevent duplicate work. See [open question on agent coordination](../../open-questions/bug_tracker-agent-coordination.md) for unresolved design gaps.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Agent Integration Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] src/lib/bugs/
[CLAUDE] ├── agent-api.ts           — shared auth + response helpers
[CLAUDE] ├── agent-cli.ts           — CLI interface
[CLAUDE] ├── agent-integration.ts   — shared integration utilities
[CLAUDE] └── mcp-server.ts          — MCP server entry point
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/chrome-extension.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 4
[CLAUDE] tags: [chrome-extension, browser-extension, evidence, auth]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Chrome Extension
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Overview
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A browser extension (`extension/`) that lets users submit bugs and attach evidence (screenshots/recordings) directly from their browser without switching to the main app.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension Files
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] extension/
[CLAUDE] ├── manifest.json    — Chrome extension manifest
[CLAUDE] ├── popup.html       — Extension popup UI
[CLAUDE] ├── popup.css        — Popup styles
[CLAUDE] └── popup.js         — Popup logic (calls extension API)
[CLAUDE] ```
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] A dedicated page at `/chrome-extension` provides installation instructions.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Extension API
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Extension requests use header-based authentication (not session cookies). The server reads auth from headers via `getAuthenticatedSessionFromExtensionRequest`.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Method | Path | Description |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/login` | Authenticate and get token |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/auth/logout` | Invalidate token |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/auth/session` | Validate current token |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/projects` | List available projects |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/bugs` | Submit a bug |
[CLAUDE] | POST | `/api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` | Upload evidence for a bug |
[CLAUDE] | GET | `/api/extension/version` | Extension version check |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Evidence Upload
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `POST /api/extension/bugs/[bugId]/evidence` requires an active testing session (`requireActiveBugTestingSession`). Evidence is stored via `attachmentStorage` and linked to the bug as an attachment.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing Sessions
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/bugs/testing-session-service.ts` manages active testing sessions. A session must be active for evidence to be uploaded — this ties extension bug submissions to a structured QA session.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
