[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/systems/bug_tracker/database.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: system
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 6
[CLAUDE] tags: [database, postgresql, schema, migrations, testing]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Database Layer
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Adapters
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app uses a **dual-database strategy**:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Backend | When used | Config |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | PostgreSQL | Production, postgres unit tests | `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND=postgres` |
[CLAUDE] | In-memory | Default unit tests | `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND=memory` |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` provides `getDatabase()` which returns the appropriate adapter. `src/lib/db/index.ts` re-exports it for use across the app.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## PostgreSQL
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Client: `pg` library (`postgres-client.ts`)
[CLAUDE] - Config: `postgres-config.ts` — reads `POSTGRES_*` env vars, defaults to `127.0.0.1:5432`
[CLAUDE] - Schema: `postgres-schema.ts` — DDL definitions
[CLAUDE] - Migrations: `scripts/migrate-postgres.ts` (run via `npm run db:migrate:postgres`)
[CLAUDE] - Worker: `postgres-worker.ts` (compiled to `.next/db/postgres-worker.mjs`) — runs DB operations off the main thread
[CLAUDE] - Bootstrap: `postgres-bootstrap.ts` — seed initial admin user
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Schema
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Defined in `src/lib/db/schema.ts` (shared types) and `src/lib/db/postgres-schema.ts` (PostgreSQL DDL).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Key tables inferred from service/store files:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Table | Purpose |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `users` | User accounts |
[CLAUDE] | `sessions` | Auth sessions |
[CLAUDE] | `auth_action_tokens` | Email verification / password reset tokens |
[CLAUDE] | `organizations` | Tenant organizations |
[CLAUDE] | `organization_memberships` | User ↔ org membership + role |
[CLAUDE] | `organization_invitations` | Pending invitations |
[CLAUDE] | `projects` | Bug projects |
[CLAUDE] | `project_sections` | Sections within projects |
[CLAUDE] | `project_memberships` | User ↔ project access |
[CLAUDE] | `bugs` | Bug records |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_comments` | Bug comments |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_attachments` | Attachment metadata |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_history` | Audit trail of bug changes |
[CLAUDE] | `bug_data_jobs` | Import/export async jobs |
[CLAUDE] | `testing_sessions` | QA testing sessions |
[CLAUDE] | `testing_session_logs` | Log entries for testing sessions |
[CLAUDE] | `notifications` | Notification event records |
[CLAUDE] | `notification_deliveries` | Per-recipient delivery records |
[CLAUDE] | `notification_settings` | Event/recipient-group enable flags |
[CLAUDE] | `operational_logs` | App observability log entries |
[CLAUDE] | `operational_alerts` | Raised operational alerts |
[CLAUDE] | `api_keys` | API key credentials |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Testing
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **In-memory**: `local-test-database.ts` + `local-test-database-runtime.ts`
[CLAUDE] - **PostgreSQL tests**: `postgres-test-setup.test.ts`, `postgres-test-reset.ts`
[CLAUDE] - Test isolation: `postgres-test-reset.ts` truncates tables between runs
[CLAUDE] - `wait-for-promise.ts` — retry helper for async DB readiness checks
[CLAUDE] 
