[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/runbooks/bug_tracker-bug-data-import.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: runbook
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 2
[CLAUDE] tags: [import, export, csv, bulk, admin]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Bug Data Import & Export
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Import
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Admin workflow:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. Prepare a CSV file with bug data
[CLAUDE] 2. Upload via Admin → Bug Data → Import
[CLAUDE] 3. System validates the CSV (row by row)
[CLAUDE] 4. Review validation result:
[CLAUDE]    - Total / valid / invalid row counts
[CLAUDE]    - Per-row issues with field + message
[CLAUDE] 5. Choose duplicate strategy: `skip_existing` or `update_existing`
[CLAUDE] 6. Execute import
[CLAUDE] 7. Monitor job status: `queued → running → completed | completed_with_warnings | failed`
[CLAUDE] 8. Review execution summary: created / updated / skipped / failed counts
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Export
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. Admin → Bug Data → Export
[CLAUDE] 2. System creates an async export job
[CLAUDE] 3. Job serializes bugs + history entries + attachments into a zip
[CLAUDE] 4. Manifest records: bugCount, historyEntryCount, attachmentCount, missingFileCount
[CLAUDE] 5. Download link available once job status is `completed`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Job Statuses
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | Status | Meaning |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|
[CLAUDE] | `queued` | Waiting to start |
[CLAUDE] | `running` | In progress |
[CLAUDE] | `completed` | Success |
[CLAUDE] | `completed_with_warnings` | Success with non-fatal issues |
[CLAUDE] | `failed` | Fatal error — check job errors array |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Troubleshooting
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - Check `job.errors` and `job.warnings` arrays on a failed job
[CLAUDE] - `missingFileCount > 0` in export manifest means some attachment files were not found on disk
[CLAUDE] - Invalid rows in import are skipped; details in `validation.rows` filtered by `issues.length > 0`
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
