[CLAUDE] === FILE: wiki/open-questions/bug_tracker-agent-coordination.md ===
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] type: open-question
[CLAUDE] owner: engineering
[CLAUDE] last_updated: 2026-04-20
[CLAUDE] source_count: 1
[CLAUDE] tags: [agent, coordination, multi-agent, concurrency]
[CLAUDE] status: active
[CLAUDE] ---
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # Open Question: Multi-Agent Coordination
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Question
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] How should multiple agents coordinate to avoid duplicate work, handle failures mid-claim, and signal progress to each other?
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Current State
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The claim mechanism (`POST /api/agent/bugs/[bugId]/claim` with `claimedBy`) provides basic mutual exclusion — an agent names itself as the claimer before working on a bug.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] However:
[CLAUDE] - There is no timeout/lease on claims — a crashed agent keeps a bug claimed indefinitely
[CLAUDE] - There is no heartbeat mechanism to signal liveness
[CLAUDE] - There is no queue abstraction — agents poll `GET /api/agent/bugs` and race to claim
[CLAUDE] - No coordination protocol is documented
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## From Source Notes
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] > "Agent should be automated and if multiple agents working on this it should coordinate with others how to perform its task."
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] This indicates multi-agent operation is intended but the coordination design is unresolved.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Options to Consider
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] 1. **Lease-based claims**: add `claimedUntil` timestamp; expired claims become available again
